To sort an `ArrayList` in Java, you can use the `Collections.sort()` method. This method sorts the elements of the list in their natural order or according to a specified comparator.

### Sorting in Natural Order

Here’s how to sort an `ArrayList` of strings or numbers in their natural order:

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Collections;

