        }
    }
}
```

### Summary

- **Theoretical Limit**: The maximum size of an array is \(2^{31} - 1\).
- **Practical Limit**: The actual limit is usually much lower due to memory constraints.
- **Configurations**: The maximum heap size of the JVM can be configured, which affects the maximum array size you can create.

