    if (n == 0 || n == 1) {
        return 1; // Directly return 1 for factorial
    }
    // Recursive case
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}
```

#### 2. Fibonacci Sequence

In the Fibonacci sequence, the simple cases are when `n` is `0` or `1`.

```java
public static int fibonacci(int n) {
    // Base case (simple case)
    if (n == 0) {
        return 0; // Fibonacci of 0
    } else if (n == 1) {
