If you want to add an element to a fixed-size array, you must create a new array with a larger size and copy the elements over. Here's how you can do that:

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] array = {1, 2, 3};
        int newValue = 4;

        // Create a new array with one extra space
        int[] newArray = new int[array.length + 1];

        // Copy the old elements to the new array
        System.arraycopy(array, 0, newArray, 0, array.length);

        // Add the new value
        newArray[newArray.length - 1] = newValue;

        // Update the reference to the new array
        array = newArray;

        // Print the updated array
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(array)); // Output: [1, 2, 3, 4]
    }
}
```

