}
```

### 3. Use Memoization

**Tip**: For problems with overlapping subproblems (like calculating Fibonacci numbers), use memoization (caching results of function calls) to improve efficiency.

**Example**:
```java
import java.util.HashMap;

public class Fibonacci {
    private static HashMap<Integer, Integer> memo = new HashMap<>();

    public static int fibonacci(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) {
            return n;
        }
        if (memo.containsKey(n)) {
            return memo.get(n);
        }
        int result = fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
        memo.put(n, result); // Cache the result
        return result;
    }
}
```

### 4. Ensure Proper Return Statements

**Tip**: Make sure that every recursive call returns a value that contributes to the final result. This may involve returning the result of the recursive call.

**Example**:
